Enum MetricLocalSetKey

    ST 1108.3 Metric Local Set tags - description and numbers.

    The Metric Local Set is a repeatable nested local set within the ST 1108.3 Interpretability and Quality Local Set.

      • Undefined

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey Undefined
        Unknown key.

        This should not be created. It is used to provide a mapping for "any other value".

      • MetricName

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricName
        Metric Name.

        The Metric Name is the name of the metric calculated.

      • MetricVersion

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricVersion
        Metric Version.

        The Metric Version mandatory item serves a dual role. Firstly, it indicates how the method used to calculate the metric, and secondly, it provides configuration management information.

      • MetricImplementer

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricImplementer
        Metric Implementer.

        The Metric Implementer mandatory item identifies the organization responsible for how a metric is calculated. This enables various versions of the same metric without having to maintain an active registry.

      • MetricParameters

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricParameters
        Optional Metric Parameters.

        Metric Parameters optional item is a user-defined string for specifying any unique conditions used in the computation.

      • MetricTime

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricTime
        Metric Time.

        Metric Time mandatory item is the time of metric assessment, which with respect to the Metric Time pack may be a future value.

      • MetricValue

        public static final MetricLocalSetKey MetricValue
        Metric Value.

        The Metric Value mandatory item is a floating-point numeric based on the resultant calculation.
